section.heading: Manufacturing and warehousing job centers account

content.p: Print RCWs > Title 82 > Chapter 82.14 > Section 82.14.550 82.14.545 << 82.14.550 >> 82.14.820 PDF RCW 82.14.550 Manufacturing and warehousing job centers account. The manufacturing and warehousing job centers account is created in the state treasury. All receipts from RCW 82.14.545 must be deposited into the account. Moneys in the account may be spent only after appropriation. Expenditures from the account may be used only for the purpose of mitigating the negative fiscal impacts to local taxing jurisdictions as a result of the streamlined sales and use tax agreement under this title. [ 2021 c 83 s 3 .] NOTES: Findings — Effective date — 2021 c 83: See notes following RCW 82.14.545 .
